The Federal Government shall have the following powers:
* Formulate and conduct the national climate change policy;
* Design, coordinate, and implement the policy instruments provided for by this Law;
* Propose, develop and publish, with the publicâs participation, the National Strategy and Program, as well as to implement, monitor and evaluate them;
* Develop, update, and publish the national risk atlas, and issue criteria to be considered in the developing of state-level risk atlases;
* In order to develop the National Strategy and Program, establish procedures for holding public consultations with the public and private sectors, and society in general;
* Establish, regulate, and implement actions on climate change mitigation and adaptation, in accordance with this Law, ratified international treaties, and all other applicable legal provisions, within the following subject matters:
	* The preservation, restoration, conservation, management, and sustainable use of natural resources, terrestrial and aquatic ecosystems, and water resources;
	* Agriculture, cattle ranching, rural development, fishing, and aquaculture;
	* Education;
	* Energy;
	* Planning of national development;
	* Food sovereignty and security;
	* Prevention of and attention to diseases resulting from the effects of climate change;
	* Civil protection;
	* Federal transportation and communications;

